              <h5 class="card-title mt-3 fw-bold">
                Water quality in Port Phillip Bay still recovering after Victoria's record floods
              </h5>
              <p class="card-text">
                Water quality in Port Phillip Bay has hit a near-decade low in the 
                wake of record rainfall, but is quickly bouncing back, environmental authorities say.
                Between 2013 and 2021, water quality in December met environmental standards around 
                90 per cent of the time across 36 bayside beaches monitored by the EPA.
              </p>
              <p class="card-text fw-semibold text-decoration-underline">
                Lenton-Williams, G. (2023, January 4). Water quality in Port Phillip Bay still recovering after Victoria’s record floods. ABC News. https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-01-05/victoria-beach-bay-water-quality-epa-melbourne-floods/101826148
              </p>
            </div>
