                Melbourne's Port Phillip Bay not suitable for swimming after severe storms
              </h5>
              <p class="card-text">
                The water quality is poor at almost 40 beaches in Port Phillip Bay following recent severe storms across Victoria.The Environment Protection 
                Authority (EPA) has warned the water is considered not suitable for swimming. The EPA says it typically takes a few days for the water to clear up but with a growing population, the issue of stormwater run-off is getting bigger. 
                <p class="card-text fw-semibold text-decoration-underline">
